  "title": "Corporate Services & Admin Executive (Healthcare)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p>\n<p>We are looking for a Corporate Admin &amp; Operations Executive who enjoys organizing, coordinating, and supporting day-to-day business activities. This role is suitable for someone early in their career who likes a mix of office administration and hands-on operations work, and wants exposure across corporate, business support and HR.</p>\n<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide comprehensive corporate and office administrative support, including preparation of business reports, tracking deadlines and maintaining organised records and filing systems.</li>\n  <li>Prepare internal memorandums and assist with business correspondence.</li>\n  <li>Process staff claims and support the execution of HR-related administrative processes.</li>\n  <li>Support day-to-day business and operations (scheduling, coordination, tracking follow-ups, clinic and office supplies control).</li>\n  <li>Maintain proper documentation to meet applicable legal and government requirements and support audits or internal reviews when needed.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / A-Level / Degree in Business administration or related field</li>\n  <li>1–3 years of experience in administrative, office support or coordination roles preferred</li>\n  <li>Fresh graduates with strong interest in corporate / admin work are welcome to apply</li>\n  <li>Comfortable with Microsoft Office / Google Workspace (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, etc.)</li>\n  <li>Good written and spoken English and Mandarin communication skills, to correspond with our China counterparts when required</li>\n  <li>Organised, meticulous and able to handle multiple tasks</li>\n  <li>Willing to be hands-on with operations and support different teams when needed</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What You Can Gain</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Exposure to corporate, HR and operations functions in a growing organization</li>\n  <li>Experience working closely with management and frontline teams</li>\n  <li>Opportunities to build strong organisational, coordination and communication skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>5-day workweek</li>\n  <li>Comprehensive medical and hospital benefits.</li>\n  <li>Generous complimentary treatments for wellness and aesthetics up to $6K per annum.</li>\n  <li>Convenient office location near to MRT stations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>📋 <strong>Application</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nComplete the form before applying:<br>\n<a href=\"https://forms.gle/BANHb1kAYwBY7k6D8\"><u>https://forms.gle/BANHb1kAYwBY7k6D8</u></a></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Pay package within the stated range will be commensurate with relevant experience and educational qualifications.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Please be advised that only candidates who have completed the form and are subsequently shortlisted will be notified.</p>",
